\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 1}.1}{\ignorespaces Schematic dependency graph for the Lean formalization effort around the Prime Number Theorem (center). Radial distance measures dependency depth and angular distance measures domain similarity as computed by namespace distance.}}{2}{figure.caption.2}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 5}.1}{\ignorespaces Publication externality (MATPG, dashed) vs.\ market internalization (MMATPG, solid) across dependency density $\rho $. Left: $\mathrm {Pub\%}$ drops sharply under credit-based rewards as dependencies increase, while the market holds it near $100\%$. Middle: PoA grows unboundedly without the market; the market keeps it below $1.25$ regardless of $\rho $. Right: resolution rate collapses without the market at high $\rho $; the market maintains near-complete resolution throughout.}}{52}{figure.caption.11}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 5}.2}{\ignorespaces PoA as a function of loss parameter $\ell $. Empirical PoA (solid) lies below the theoretical bound $(2-1/m)/(1-\ell )$ (dashed) throughout, validating the $1/(1-\ell )$ friction factor. At $\ell =0$ the market is a pure bounty system; at $\ell =0.5$ market friction visibly increases equilibrium cost.}}{52}{figure.caption.12}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 5}.3}{\ignorespaces Training dynamics over population iterations. Left: exploitability tracks $O(1/\sqrt {T})$ reference. Middle: PoA converges toward the theoretical bound of $1.67$. Right: entropy annealing avoids premature convergence.}}{53}{figure.caption.13}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 5}.4}{\ignorespaces Rollout behavior statistics over PSRO training. Publication rate rises as agents internalize market incentives; market participation overshoots then stabilizes as trading becomes more deliberate; idle rate falls as agents learn productive task sequences. Together these confirm that the market externality is being learned away, not just suppressed.}}{53}{figure.caption.14}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 5}.5}{\ignorespaces Population meta-strategy evolution over PSRO iterations. Weights spread across diverse best-response policies in the middle phase (validating opponent diversity) before reconcentrating on robust generalist policies as the meta-game converges.}}{54}{figure.caption.15}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 5}.6}{\ignorespaces Best-response quality over PSRO iterations}}{55}{figure.caption.16}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 5}.7}{\ignorespaces Scaling with agent count $m$. Left: PoA ratio vs.\ $m$; all decentralized policies remain below the theoretical bound. Right: absolute makespan vs.\ $m$; MARL tracks centralized RLS despite operating without a planner.}}{57}{figure.caption.21}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 6}.1}{\ignorespaces Agora platform architecture. Library Mechanics owns Lean validation; Market Mechanics owns financial invariants; the Backend Interface exposes MCP tools to LLM agents. The Agent Orchestrator provisions containers and seeds the market.}}{62}{figure.caption.23}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 6}.2}{\ignorespaces Comparison between the extracted Prime Number Theorem utility graph and derived synthetic utility graphs sampled across decreasing game sizes.}}{70}{figure.caption.24}%
