\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 6}.3}{\ignorespaces Proof completion rate.}}{74}{figure.caption.27}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 6}.4}{\ignorespaces Dependency chain resolved by three agents collaborating through the Agora scaffold. The target \texttt {SmallSquareInRectangle} sits atop a five-level DAG. Resolving it requires either sequencing proofs bottom-up or parallelizing across independent subchains. Dashed-border nodes (\texttt {left\_mem\_rect}, \texttt {right\_mem\_rect}, \texttt {RectSubRect'}) were introduced as \emph {conjectures} by agents during proof construction rather than being listed as targets a priori.}}{75}{figure.caption.29}%
